littleIf smart products help you control home appliance.You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light.

There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust you home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 
After connecting Alexa to your littlelf Smart products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "littlelf Smart" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register one littlelf Smart account in our "littlelf Smart" app;
(3). You need to have some littlelf Smart devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our littlelf Smart" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "littlelf Smart" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "littlelf smart" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "littlelf Smart", and you'll be navigated to littlelf login page;
(9). Input your littlelf account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
"Alexa, turn on smart plug"
"Alexa,turn off smart plug"

Currently this skill supports products:
smart camera
smart plug
